Results on Biobank Japan

Yongjin Park

2018-06-20

Summary statistics data can be downloaded from JENGER.

We trained our summary-based factored regression models on 1,445 LD blocks independently, of which boundaries were approximately estimated (Berisa and Pickrell 2016) based on the 1000 genomes project reference panel of Asian population (The 1000 Genomes Project Consortium et al. 2015).

We identified 129 SNP factors are significantly associated with multiple traits (PIP cutoff 0.9) from 110 LD blocks, spanning over 253 Mb that corresponds to 9% of genome.

We then clustered these factors into 37 clusters according to the similarity of multi-trait activities (log-odds ratio).
